meanings.definition: To kick or strike with greater force or distance than something else.
meanings.sent1: He tried to outkick his friend in the soccer match.
meanings.sent2: She managed to outkick the ball all the way to the goal.
meanings.sent3: The little dog attempted to outkick the big dog in play.
meanings.sent4: The determined athlete aimed to outkick all his competitors in the race.
meanings.sent5: With a powerful swing, he outkicked the ball into the net.

meanings.definition: To surpass or exceed in performance or achievement.
meanings.sent1: The student wanted to outkick his previous test score.
meanings.sent2: She always strives to outkick her own expectations.
meanings.sent3: The chef tried to outkick her previous culinary masterpiece.
meanings.sent4: The team worked hard to outkick their opponents in the final game.
meanings.sent5: The artist's new painting outkicked all her previous works.
